 P(X \text{ is even} ) = e^{-\lambda} \cdot \sum_{k=0}^{+\infty} \frac{\lambda^{2k}}{(2k)!}
e^\lambda = \sum_{n = 0}^{+\infty} \lambda^n/n!
P(X \text{ is even})
\displaystyle f(\lambda)= \sum_{k\ge0}\frac{\lambda^{2k}}{(2k)!}
f''(\lambda) = f(\lambda)
f(0)=1
f'(0)=0
 f(\lambda) = \frac{e^\lambda+e^{-\lambda}}{2} = \cosh(\lambda). 
\Pr(\text{even}) = \dfrac{1+e^{-2\lambda}}{2}
